# Git and documentation

## Do not commit

- `docs/TECHNICAL.md`, `docs/MVP.md`, `docs/LINEAR.md` — internal planning (gitignored)
- `.env`, credentials, real user memory exports
- `.obsidian/`, `node_modules/`, `dist/`

## Public docs

- `README.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `LICENSE`
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — contributor-facing design overview

## Commits

Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `chore:`

## Pull requests (solo project)

- **Do not reply to PR review comments** — no thread replies, no `gh api` comment posts, no review responses on GitHub unless the user explicitly asks.
- Triage review feedback in chat: fix valid issues in code, push back on invalid ones in the conversation.
- Creating/updating PRs and pushing branches is fine when requested; engaging reviewers on GitHub is not.
